### Instructions for Sending the Email:

1. **Email Client or Service**: Use an email client (like Outlook, Gmail) that allows you to send HTML emails. Or, you can use a programming language (like Python with `smtplib`) to send the email.

2. **Sending the Email**:
   - Set the recipient as `contact@contact.com`.
   - Set the subject line as needed (e.g., "Confirmation Email").
   - Use the HTML code for the email body in your email-sending script or client.

### Example using Python:

If you want to send the email programmatically using Python, here’s a small example:

```python
import smtplib
from email.mime.multipart import MIMEMultipart
from email.mime.text import MIMEText

# Set up the server
smtp_server = 'smtp.your-email-provider.com'
smtp_port = 587
username = 'your_email@example.com'
password = 'your_password'

# Set up the email parameters
to_email = 'contact@contact.com'
subject = 'Confirmation Email'

# Create the email
msg = MIMEMultipart()
msg['From'] = username
msg['To'] = to_email
msg['Subject'] = subject

# HTML content
html = """<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Email Confirmation</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        .email-container {
            background-color: #ffffff;
            border-radius: 5px;
            padding: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }
        h1 {
            color: #333;
        }
        p {
            color: #666;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="email-container">
        <h1>Confirmation</h1>
        <p>This is a confirmation email.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>"""

# Attach the HTML content to the email
msg.attach(MIMEText(html, 'html'))

# Send the email
with smtplib.SMTP(smtp_server, smtp_port) as server:
    server.starttls()
    server.login(username, password)
    server.sendmail(username, to_email, msg.as_string())

print("Email sent successfully.")
```

Make sure to replace `smtp.your-email-provider.com`, `your_email@example.com`, and `your_password` with actual values specific to your email provider.

### Note:
Regardless of the method you choose, ensure you have necessary permissions to send emails, comply with anti-spam regulations, and handle errors appropriately.

